  <RhapsodyProfile:RhpModelElement xmi:id="GUID+95c56903-e092-4f0c-b0a1-2a2fa034c479_Stereotype_RhapsodyProfile_RhpModelElement" guid="GUID 95c56903-e092-4f0c-b0a1-2a2fa034c479" description="The purpose of this stereotype, is to enable a 'BluePrint' mechanism. A user can create an exemplar as he desires, then creates a new term stereotype of a certain type, and add to that stereotype a dependency with the the 'StandardContent' stereotype to the exemplar he created. Upon creation of the new term element, rhapsody will merge the new element with the exemplar." descriptionHTML="&lt;![[CDATA[The purpose of this stereotype, is to enable a 'BluePrint' mechanism. A user can create an exemplar as he desires, then creates a new term stereotype of a certain type, and add to that stereotype a dependency with the the 'StandardContent' stereotype to the exemplar he created. Upon creation of the new term element, rhapsody will merge the new element with the exemplar.]]>" descriptionRTF="&lt;![[CDATA[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg1255\deff0\deflang1037{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}&#xD;&#xA;\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\fs20 The purpose of this stereotype, is to enable a 'BluePrint' mechanism. A user can create an exemplar as he desires, then creates a new term stereotype of a certain type, and add to that stereotype a dependency with the the 'StandardContent' stereotype to the exemplar he created. Upon creation of the new term element, rhapsody will merge the new element with the exemplar.\par&#xD;&#xA;}&#xD;&#xA;]]>" base_Stereotype="GUID+95c56903-e092-4f0c-b0a1-2a2fa034c479" base_Class="GUID+95c56903-e092-4f0c-b0a1-2a2fa034c479"/>
